The paper proposes a novel approach to representation learning on graphs using message passing neural networks. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed algorithm involves asynchronous message passing and utilizes a node-adaptive receptive field, which suggests the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and signal processing (cs.SI). The empirical evaluation involves semi-supervised node classification, which could also fall under computer vision (cs.CV) if the graphs represent images.
